17 shall place an advertisement in a newspaper of general circulation serving the residents
18 of the political subdivision and post such advertisement on its public website, which shall
19 read as follows:
20 'INTENT TO OPT OUT OF HOMESTEAD EXEMPTION
21 The (name of governing authority) intends to opt out of the statewide state-wide
22 adjusted base year ad valorem homestead exemption for (name of the political
23 subdivision).
24 All concerned citizens are invited to the public hearing on this matter to be held at
25 (place of meeting) on (date and time).
26 Times and places of additional public hearings on this matter are at (place of meeting)
27 on (date and time).'
28 Simultaneously with this notice, the governing authority shall provide a press release to
29 the local media.
30 (2) The advertisement required by paragraph (1) of this subsection shall appear at least
31 one week prior to each hearing, be prominently displayed, be not less than 30 square
32 inches, and not be placed in that section of the newspaper where legal notices appear and
33 shall be posted on the appropriate public website at least one week prior to each hearing.
34 In addition to the advertisement specified under this paragraph, the levying or
35 recommending authority may include in the notice reasons or explanations for its
36 intention to opt out of the homestead exemption.
37 (3) No resolution to opt out of the homestead exemption shall become effective with
38 respect to a political subdivision unless the procedures and hearings required by this
39 subsection are completed and a copy of such resolution is filed with the Secretary of State
40 by March May 1, 2025."
41 SECTION 2.
42 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
